%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20robotics%20startup%20cofounder%20shares%20why%20most%20robots%20likely%20won't%20need%20legs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224699%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Vivian%20Chu%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68d4a396183847aa39d76c38%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222350%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVivian%20Chu%2C%20co-founder%20and%20CTO%20of%20Diligent%20Robotics%2C%20told%20BI%20humanoid%20robots%20have%20potential%20but%20are%20still%20ways%20away%20in%20the%20future.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Diligent%20Robotics%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EVivian%20Chu%20is%20the%20cofounder%20and%20CTO%20of%20Diligent%20Robotics%2C%20maker%20of%20Moxi%2C%20the%20robot.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMoxi%20is%20a%20wheeled%20robot%20that%20helps%20hospital%20staff%20with%20tasks%20such%20as%20delivering%20supplies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChu%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20wheeled%20form%20factor%20will%20likely%20cover%20most%20needs%20for%20companies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20the%20two-legged%20humanoid%20robot%20has%20brought%20bold%20visions%20from%20industry%20leaders%20like%20Tesla%20or%20Figure.AI%20of%20highly%20intelligent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffigure-ai-founder-brett-adcock-humanoid-robots-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erobot%20servants%3C%2Fa%3E%20unlocking%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-humanoid-robots-ai-benefits-optimus-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elimitless%20economic%20potential%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20little-known%20startup%20out%20in%20Austin%20says%20not%20so%20fast%3A%20The%20wheeled%20robot%20is%20fine%20for%20most%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffemale-led-robotics-startup-diligent-raises-seed-funding-2019-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDiligent%20Robotics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20Austin-based%20startup%20founded%20in%202017%2C%20builds%20robots%20for%20the%20healthcare%20space.%20Its%20wheeled%20robot%2C%20Moxi%2C%20can%20automate%20tasks%20in%20the%20hospital%2C%20such%20as%20delivering%20lab%20samples%20or%20medical%20supplies.%20These%20are%20routine%20but%20essential%20chores%20that%20Vivian%20Chu%2C%20co-founder%20of%20Diligent%20Robotics%2C%20says%20take%20precious%20time%20away%20from%20human%20staff%20and%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20think%20that%20over%20time%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20very%20quickly%20see%20that%20the%20wheel%20form%20factor%20%E2%80%94%20like%20two%20arms%2C%20a%20head%2C%20and%20a%20wheel%20%E2%80%94%20is%20probably%20going%20to%20be%20a%20form%20factor%20that%20ends%20up%20covering%20the%20majority%20of%20what%20you%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20Chu%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Moxi%2C%20don't%20think%20of%20a%20humanoid%20robot%20installed%20with%20the%20latest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChatGPT%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20carrying%20out%20free-flowing%20dialogue.%20Chu%20likes%20to%20think%20of%20Moxi%20more%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bminimum%20viable%20humanoid%26quot%3B%20whittled%20down%20to%20focus%20on%20specific%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20Moxi%20is%20simple%20to%20build%20or%20any%20less%20useful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20more%20than%2090%20robots%20deployed%20across%2025%2B%20hospitals%2C%20Chu%20told%20BI%20that%20Diligent's%20Moxi%20robots%20have%20carried%20out%20over%201.2%20million%20supply%20deliveries.%20The%20company%20estimates%20that%20that%20equates%20to%20about%20half%20a%20million%20hours%20of%20human%20time%20saved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20Chu%20about%20how%20Diligent%20Robotics%20is%20meeting%20hospitals'%20needs%2C%20where%20the%20technology%20needs%20improvements%2C%20and%20why%20humanoid%20robots%20are%20a%20ways%20away%20from%20entering%20our%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20interview%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20you%20get%20into%20robotics%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area%20with%20classic%20engineering%20parents.%20In%20my%20senior%20year%20at%20Berkeley%2C%20I%20took%20my%20first%20intro%20to%20robotics%20class%2C%20where%20I%20got%20to%20program%20a%20robot.%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BDamn%20it%2C%20I%20want%20to%20learn%20more.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20went%20to%20Penn%20for%20a%20master's%20and%20then%20to%20Georgia%20Tech%20for%20a%20PhD.%20That's%20where%20I%20met%20my%20cofounder%2C%20Andrea%20Thomaz%2C%20who%20was%20my%20PhD%20advisor.%20She's%20a%20leading%20world%20expert%20on%20how%20to%20put%20robots%20and%20people%20together.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20met%20her%2C%20we%20were%20both%20at%20the%20stage%20of%20life%20where%20we%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BRobots%20are%20cool.%20We%20write%20our%20papers%20about%20them%2C%20we%20do%20one%20lab%20experiment%2C%20and%20then%20we%20just%20go.%26quot%3B%20But%20we%20wanted%20robots%20to%20actually%20make%20a%20difference%2C%20like%20we%20said%20in%20our%20papers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20decided%20that%20the%20technology%20was%20starting%20to%20get%20ready.%20When%20Andrea%20first%20started%20our%20lab%2C%20a%20robot%20cost%20half%20a%20million%20dollars.%20By%202015%2C%202016%2C%20you%20could%20build%20the%20same%20robot%20for%20%2480%2C000%20to%20%24100%2C00.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20now%2C%20the%20cost%20has%20dramatically%20gone%20down.%20That's%20when%20we%20decided%20to%20start%20Diligent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20hospitals%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20did%20about%20100%20to%20150%20interviews%20across%20the%20market.%20Really%20quickly%2C%20we%20homed%20in%20on%20healthcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%20days%2C%20we%20shadowed%20nurses%20and%20staff%20with%20clipboards%20and%20stopwatches%20to%20see%20where%20robots%20could%20make%20a%20difference.%20Even%20before%20COVID%2C%20we%20found%20that%20nurses%20and%20clinicians%20spend%20up%20to%2030%25%20of%20their%20time%20just%20fetching%20and%20gathering%20supplies%2C%20and%20less%20than%2030%25%20on%20direct%20patient%20care%20because%20they're%20so%20busy%20with%20logistical%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20time%20returned%20to%20a%20staff%20member%20meant%20better%20patient%20outcomes.%20We%20saw%20that%20and%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20where%20robots%20should%20be.%20This%20is%20how%20you%20think%20about%20robots%20augmenting%20people%20as%20opposed%20to%20replacing%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20you%20decide%20on%20Moxi's%20design%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20were%20fundraising%20early%20in%202017%2C%20investors%20would%20ask%20us%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20do%20you%20have%20an%20arm%20on%20your%20robot%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20us%2C%20it%20was%20a%20no-brainer.%20If%20you%20don't%2C%20hospitals%20would%20have%20to%20modify%20every%20single%20door%20and%20elevator.%20Retrofitting%20a%20hospital%20could%20cost%20a%20million%20dollars%20and%20could%20take%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20an%20arm%2C%20Moxi%20can%20just%20push%20the%20elevator%20button%20directly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20head%20is%20important%20too.%20We're%20putting%20robots%20in%20a%20place%20where%20people%20have%20never%20interacted%20with%20a%20robot.%20Things%20like%20eye%20contact%2C%20or%20if%20I'm%20looking%20at%20my%20cup%2C%20you%20know%20I'm%20going%20to%20drink%20my%20coffee.%20A%20head%20means%20the%20robot%20can%20communicate%20intent.%20Our%20main%20sensor%20for%20manipulation%20is%20in%20the%20head%2C%20so%20every%20time%20it%20looks%2C%20it's%20actively%20perceiving%20and%20communicating%20intent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20wheels%2C%20hospitals%20are%20ADA-compliant.%20They%20have%20ramps%20and%20automated%20doors.%20Going%20with%20a%20wheel%20form%20factor%20made%20sense.%20It%20is%20statistically%20stable%2C%20safe%2C%20and%20perfect%20for%20an%20environment%20with%20elevators%20and%20ramps.%20If%20something%20happens%20and%20you%20power%20down%2C%20you%20can%20just%20roll%20the%20robot%20to%20the%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20hospitals%20measure%20success%20with%20Moxi%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETime%20and%20steps%20saved%20are%20probably%20the%20first%20basic%20metrics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20our%20hospital%20systems%20had%20teleboxes%20%E2%80%94%20these%20are%20bedside%20monitors%20that%20monitor%20a%20patient's%20vital%20signs%20and%20have%20to%20be%20sent%20around%20constantly.%20After%20we%20installed%20Moxi%2C%20now%20every%20single%20telemetry%20box%20in%20three%20massive%20buildings%20is%20sent%20through%20the%20robot.%20There%20are%20now%20zero%20people%20who%20run%20the%20boxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20Moxi%20has%20made%20over%201.2%20million%20deliveries.%20Based%20on%20average%20distance%20and%20tasks%2C%20we%20estimate%20that%20staff%20would've%20saved%20around%20half%20a%20million%20hours%20of%20time%20walking%20equipment%2C%20lab%20samples%2C%20or%20medication%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20you%20think%20humanoid%2C%20legged%20robots%20are%20coming%20soon%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20see%20that%20the%20form%20factor%20with%20a%20head%2C%20two%20arms%2C%20and%20wheels%20is%20probably%20going%20to%20cover%20the%20majority%20of%20tasks.%20There%20is%20an%20interesting%20segment%20where%20you%20do%20need%20legs%20%E2%80%94%20disaster%20recovery%20is%20one%20that%20comes%20to%20mind%2C%20or%20homes%20where%20you%20have%20stairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20comes%20down%20to%20the%20workflow.%20What%20is%20the%20pain%20point%3F%20What%20can%20robots%20be%20doing%2024%2F7%20that%20truly%20gives%20people%20their%20time%20back%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20be%20very%20premature%20to%20talk%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-testing-humanoid-robots-digit-warehouses-agility-robotics-boston-dynamics-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elegged%20robots%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20the%20thing%20that%20a%20warehouse%20needs%20might%20not%20require%20legs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20legged%20form%20factor%20in%20homes%20%E2%80%94%20I%20see%20it%20pretty%20far%2C%20far%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20have%20investor%20conversations%20changed%20in%20light%20of%20recent%20focus%C2%A0on%20bipedal%20humanoid%20robots%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20beginning%2C%20investors%20would%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20do%20you%20have%20an%20arm%3F%26quot%3B%20Now%20they%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20don't%20you%20have%20two%20arms%3F%26quot%3B%20And%20there%20are%20tasks%20that%20will%20require%20a%20second%20arm%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20on%20our%20future%20roadmap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20some%20education%20you%20have%20to%20do%20with%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20do%20you%20go%20all%20in%20on%20general-purpose%2C%20or%20focus%20on%20a%20specific%20segment%3F%20With%20all%20deep%20tech%2C%20you%20just%20have%20to%20find%20the%20right%20investors%20who%20understand%20the%20thesis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAny%20broader%20advancements%20in%20robots%20you're%20looking%20out%20for%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBattery%20technology.%20Our%20robots%20last%20about%2016%20hours%20total%20with%20smart%20charging%20in%20between.%20As%20we%20scale%20compute%2C%20power%20becomes%20the%20bottleneck.%20I%20think%20some%20of%20these%20humanoid%20companies%20only%20have%20a%2090-minute%20runtime.%20Then%20there's%20safety%3A%20Hospitals%20care%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20safety%20of%20your%20platform%2C%20like%20whether%20it%20could%20catch%20on%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20what%20I'd%20love%20to%20see%20innovation%20in%20%E2%80%94%20safer%2C%20longer-lasting%20batteries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E